Note: Asserting session DB status (e.g., "error" vs "halted") requires
the session ID, which is not exposed by Run()'s return value. These
assertions rely on halt code parity (HaltQuota/HaltAuth → "error" in
haltCodeToStatus) rather than direct DB queries. No source modification
was made.

Area 5 — Session-reuse correctness (3 tests):
  - TestTester_SessionReuse_MultipleHalts: Calls Run() twice with timeout
    errors. First Run() creates session, triggers resumeSession. Second
    Run() detects resume_summary, times out again. halt2.ResumeCount >= 1.
    PASS.
  - TestTester_ResumeUsesSummaryNotReplay: Captures the LLM request on
    the resumed call. Verifies: (a) message[1] contains "Previous session",
    (b) does NOT contain original kickoff "Implement feature X.",
    (c) exactly 2 messages (system + summary, NOT a full replay). PASS.
  - TestTester_ResumeShowsFileData: Makes 3 edits to main.go + 1 to
