=== Tester entry — Fix Cycle 2 (2026-07-06) ===

Result: PASS

E2E PASS: agent-harness Phase 3 Fix Cycle 2 — all scenarios green
Toolchain: Go
Deployment: NATIVE (go test)

Test: TestTester_SymlinkWithGlobRestriction (NEW — Area 7)

Added to internal/loop/tester_phase3_test.go:
A combined symlink+active-glob-restriction test that exercises the exact
bug described in ADR §14. The test:

1. Creates a real directory with docs/readme.md (matching path) and
   other/note.md (non-matching path) inside it.
2. Creates a symlink pointing to the real directory.
3. Builds a registry and TurnLoop through the symlink, with an agent config
   restricting edit_file to glob "docs/*.md".
4. The Fake LLM responds with two edit_file calls in one turn:
   - edit_file("docs/readme.md") — should match the glob
   - edit_file("other/note.md") — should NOT match the glob
5. After the run, verifies:
   - docs/readme.md content was CHANGED (proof the glob was matched correctly
     and the tool executed) — this would have FAILED pre-fix because AllowPath
     computed filepath.Rel against the unresolved symlink root, producing a
     wrong relative path that no glob could match.
   - other/note.md content was UNCHANGED (proof the glob correctly rejected
     a non-matching path).

Pre-fix failure confirmed via standalone simulation:
   ToolConfig.ProjectRoot = symDir (unresolved, pre-fix behavior)
   → filepath.Rel produces wrong relative path
   → DisallowedPathError on MATCHING path (false negative)
   → docs/readme.md not edited

   ToolConfig.ProjectRoot = resolvedRoot (post-fix behavior)
   → filepath.Rel produces correct relative path
   → Glob matches, tool executes
   → docs/readme.md content changed to "new content" ✓

Regression verification:
- Spot-checked newFixtureWithCfg in loop_test.go: correctly captures
  resolvedRoot from NewDefaultRegistry return value (line 89), passes to
  New() (line 96). ✓
- Spot-checked e2e/phase2_test.go line 32: correctly discards second
  return value with `_`. ✓
- Full suite: go test -count=1 ./... passes all 5 packages:
  e2e: PASS, internal/llm: PASS, internal/loop: 44 tests PASS,
  internal/store: PASS, internal/tools: PASS

Conclusion: Fix Cycle 2 is structurally sound. The signature change on
NewDefaultRegistry ensures the resolved root is computed in exactly one
place and flows to both consumers (tools + loop) from that single source,
making the caller-convention vulnerability described in ADR §14.1
structurally impossible.

Phase 3 is ready to merge per §15.
